  "title": "Impact of parental ages and other characteristics at childbearing on congenital anomalies",
  "abstract": "While it is widely known that maternal age at childbearing plays a role in the occurrence of Down syndrome, less is known about the effects of maternal age on other major congenital anomalies. Information on the possible effects of other maternal characteristics and of the age of the father is even scarcer.",
